     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "## Compare numbers of 2-block light curves with the single blocks\n",
       "There are two reasons for 2-BB light curves to be  related to the 1-BB ones.\n",
       "1) Background: It is a false positive generated by the\n",
       "BB algorithm. (We need to examine this possibility with a MC.)\n",
       "2) Science: The source must have been quiet for at least 8 years, compared with 15 for \n",
       "the 1-block set. The rates must be part of same variability spectrum.\n",
       "\n",
       "Here is a plot of the 1- abd 2-block fractions for each of our six \n",
       "association classes:"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<utilities.ipynb_docgen.doc_formatter.<locals>.MimeBundleObject at 0xfcdb713e02c0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div style=\"margin-left: 10px\"><a id=\"Figure_None\"/><figure style=\"margin-left: 10px\">   <img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"  > <br>  <figcaption>Scatter plot showing the relative frequencies of 1- and 2-block light curves for\n",
       "    each asociation type.\n",
       "    \n",
       "    </figcaption></figure></div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<utilities.ipynb_docgen.doc_formatter.<locals>.MimeBundleObject at 0xfcdb714ca870>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "### The distributions of the sizes of the steps.\n",
       "The pulsar one should only reflect reason 1."
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<utilities.ipynb_docgen.doc_formatter.<locals>.MimeBundleObject at 0xfcdb7101fd40>"
